--- caveats (raw#10 C3) ---
  1. CLI surface limited: 6 subcmds expose ~core ~10% of qmirror functionality
     (chsh/qrng/iit/phi advanced flags reachable only via direct hexa run).
  2. Real-QPU subcommands (chsh --vendor=ionq|rigetti|ibm) require API keys
     in env (IONQ_API_KEY, etc); without keys → mock fallback only.
  3. selftest assumes infrastructure intact — _python_bridge present, ANU mock
     fixtures readable, Braket fixture dir exists; missing → individual F* FAIL.
  4. Future cond additions need router updates — current 8/8 cond hardcoded;
     adding cond.9+ requires editing cli/qmirror.hexa dispatcher.
  5. Standalone-extraction caveat: env vars still NEXUS_QMIRROR_* prefixed (load-bearing
     for backward compat); QMIRROR_* alias migration deferred to sister cycle.
